The building was not suitable for the museum, either spatially or technically - there were no walls for hanging art exhibits, no suitable climate.
Nevertheless, it was used until contemporary art got a new booth in Vienna.
Since 2001, the building has been empty and deteriorating more and more.
Now the architect Adolf Krischanitz has renovated the pavilion, now bearing the name "House of the 21st century" and will be used as a Museum of Contemporary Art in the future.
