Three properties and a cell phone were seized, and they confirmed they were members of a criminal group called Los Zetas.
Another raid occurred at 6am on November 12th, when military personnel were on patrol in the Rancho Viejo area of Cadereyta when they noticed a car with no license plate and two people inside.
After the car was stopped, they searched the premises and found one rifle, a magazine, and 18 rounds.
Then, based on these statements, one of the accomplices was arrested on November 13th at around 2pm in the area of La Frauda.
