There was an eviction of a foreclosed house where huge parties were being held.
The intruders have taken 11 of the 13 apartments in the building in Balmes, 51.
12 occupants left the house yesterday at noon without resisting
All indications are that the nightmare experienced by the neighbours of 51 Balmes Street is finally over.
Twelve people voluntarily left the building they were illegally occupying yesterday at noon, where they were throwing a huge party that woke up the neighbors, leaving the building by court order and without the need for police intervention.
After the operation, the lock on the door was replaced to prevent a repeat.
"From this moment on, the entrance will be guarded", declared the warden.
The occupants, who took 11 of the 13 apartments in the building - the rest are residential - took away all electrical and some water supplies, painted the walls, and left behind trash of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
In the first three apartments, huge parties were held that lasted for up to two days and woke up the other tenants.
There's a disco next to the building, Balmes 51, which was also damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that during the time the building was occupied, sales had fallen by 80%.
The owner of the club claims that the occupants of the building were unfairly competing with her, because they sold drinks for 3 euros, whereas the disco costs 10.
The owner of the entertainment business also had to respond to complaints from neighbors about noise, but the problem was not with the visitors to the club, but with the residents of the house, especially those who attended the parties, which have increased in frequency and intensity in recent weeks, according to angry residents.
