By 2017, the public structural deficit will have to be reduced by 0,75% of gross domestic product (GDP) each year and, from 2017, the federal government's structural deficit will not exceed 0,35% of GDP each year, while the Länder, as well as the municipalities, will have to report a balanced budget.
The objective is to bring public debt below the 60% criterion set by the Maastricht Treaty by 2020/21.
